This paper deals with communication channels and their capacity, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The presence of an active adversary also suggests a security aspect, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of relaying in communication systems is also a topic in networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The consideration of input and state constraints suggests a control systems aspect (cs.SY), and the use of Gaussian channels suggests a signal processing aspect (cs.MM).
